{"key": "p1_2", "rev": 2, "text": "13. The purpose Practice of this practice is to turn the attention of the mind towards your breathing body. In this practice, we navigate the mind from thoughts to the breathing process, to observing the breath and sensations within the body. We set ourselves to take the time to keep driving the mind from thinking to breathing. Let us begin the process of self and breathing observation. Identify your precise location. Let's start by turning the mind inward towards your breath. Notice the flow of the breath. Turn your mind towards the breathing process. Notice the air coming out of your body. Start observing the breathing process. Notice the exhale. The inhale. Mind towards the breathing. Let's start observing the breath. From thinking to breathing. Let's start observing the breath. From thought to breath. Turn your mind towards the breathing process. Let's start observing the breathing process. Turn your mind towards the breathing. Observe your breathing process. Allow your body to breathe freely and naturally as it requires. Let's start observing the breath. Watch the natural breathing process of your body. Notice the flow of the breath. Let's start observing the breath. From thought to breath. From emotion to breath. From thought to breath. Back to the breathing body. Back to the breathing. From thought to breath. Observe the free and natural breathing of your body. Observe the breathing. We have nothing else to do. Observe the sensations inside your body. Continue observing. Observe observing. Back to the breath. From thought to breath. Observe Observe your natural breathing. Observe observing. From thought to breath. Wait and observe. Observe. Observe. Observe. Observe. Keep your back straight. Observe. Observe. Keep your back straight. Observe.  Keep breathing by itself.  Witness your breath. Observe. Just you. Witness breath or nonmen breath. Your presence. Observe. Your breath. Your presence. Observe.", "segments": [{"id": 0